<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-03-26T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-03-26T10:00:00-05:00" n="203" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d203">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/2054: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at Arica</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Von
                                    Tresckow</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-03-26T10:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 26,
                                        1926—10 a.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>For Lassiter. Your telegram March 25, 3 p.m., received. I wholly approve
                            position you took in proceedings yesterday and think that the formal
                            record at this time is satisfactory. I shall send further suggestions,
                            especially with regard to the resolution for the suspension of
                            proceedings, as soon as replies have been received from Santiago and
                            Lima, as stated in my telegram of March 25, 6 p.m.<note n="36" xml:id="d203fn36">See footnote 32, <ref target="#pg_350">p.
                                    350</ref>.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>